Defendant in custody on WRIT.  
State moves to delete the penalty enhancer on count 1.   Motion granted.  
Count 1 - Armed Robbery - No contest plea.   Convicted.   State moves to dismiss and read in count 2, armed robbery as repeater.   Motion granted.   Defendant is sentenced to the Wisconsin State Prison System for a total senence of thirteen (13) years, consecutive to the sentence defendant is serving out of Brown County on 14 CF 1494.  Seven (7) years initial confinement, followed by six (6) years extended supervision.   Conditions of extended supervision are:
1) Maintain full-time employment/schooling combination;
2) Pay costs of action; 
3) Assessment/treatment/counseling as deemed appropriate by the Department's assessment process;
4) Pay supervision fees in an amount to be determined by DOC;
5) Pay restitution of $232.00 to Wells Fargo; 
6) Submit DNA sample;
7) Court finds financial obligations shall be paid at the rate of 25% of the prison wages and work release funds.   The balance remaining at release from prison to be paid as a condition of extended supervision at a rate determined by the supervising agent.   
Court finds the defendant is not eligible for the challenge incarceration program or the earned release program.   
